      "created": "2017-08-15T18:58:18.339+0000",
      "description": "*PROBLEM*\nHow to enable preemption on a single queue in a cluster?\n*DESCRIPTION*\nAs of today the only way to enable preemption at a queue level is:\n* Enable cluster level preemption\n* Disable preemption on the queues where not required using yarn.scheduler.capacity.<queue-path>.disable_preemption to true\n\nCan we have some sort of a parameter like \n*_yarn.scheduler.capacity.<queue-path>.enable_preemption_*\nwhich would just enable preemption per queue instead of going the other way round which is more time consuming and error prone.\n\n",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
      "resolution": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/resolution/1",
        "id": "1",
        "description": "A fix for this issue is checked into the tree and tested.",
        "name": "Fixed"
      },
